Kafka Architecture - Part 2: Key Concepts

This video focuses on essential components of Kafka's architecture, including consumer groups, offset management, and the Kafka cluster.

Consumer and Consumer Groups

Consumers read data from Kafka topics.
Consumer groups organize consumers.
Rule 1: Consumers in the same group read different partitions.
Rule 2: Consumers in different groups can read the same partition.
Offset Commits

Kafka tracks the progress of each consumer group using offsets.
This information is stored in an internal topic: _consumer_offsets.
Storing offsets group-wise (not consumer-wise) ensures seamless takeover if a consumer fails.
When a new consumer starts, it can fetch the last processed offset for its group and partition from _consumer_offsets.
Offset Commit Strategies

Auto-commit:
Commits offsets automatically at set intervals.
Risk: Data loss can occur if a consumer crashes before processing events but after the offset has been auto-committed.
Manual commit (recommended):
Allows consumers to decide when to commit offsets.
Batch commit: Process a batch of events, then commit the offset for the entire batch. This reduces duplicate processing upon crash.
Per-event commit: Committing after every single event is generally not recommended due to increased overhead, especially with high event volumes.
Kafka Cluster

A Kafka cluster is a group of brokers working together.
It provides:
Scalability: Distributes load across multiple servers.
Fault tolerance: Continues operating even if a broker fails.
High availability: No single point of failure.
Leader-Follower Partition Architecture

For each partition, one broker is designated as the leader, and others are followers.
Leader responsibilities:
Handles all producer writes and consumer reads for that partition.
Maintains the partition logs.
Coordinates with followers.
Follower responsibilities:
Replicate data from the leader.
Stay in sync with the leader.
Are ready to become a leader if the current leader fails.
Do not serve clients directly; only the leader does.
